2.2:
Earth's kings take their stand;
its rulers band together—
against the LORD and against his Anointed One.

2.7:
Let me announce the LORD's decree:
He said to me, 'You are my Son;
this very day I have fathered you.'

5.1:
To the worship leader: for flutes. A Psalm of David.

Listen to my words, O LORD;
hear the sounds beneath them—the sighing I cannot fully voice.

5.3:
At dawn my voice reaches you, LORD;
I lay my prayer before you at first light
and watch for your answer.

5.6:
You bring ruin on every liar;
the LORD detests those whose hands are bloodstained
and whose tongue trades in deceit.

5.8:
Guide me in your righteousness, LORD,
because my enemies watch for any misstep;
smooth your path so it runs straight before me.

5.9:
No word of theirs can be trusted;
their hearts are a wasteland;
their throat gapes like an open grave;
smooth words flow from a tongue that deceives.

6.1:
To the worship leader: for stringed instruments, the eighth. A Psalm of David.

LORD, do not correct me in your fury;
do not discipline me when your anger is burning.

6.6:
I am worn out with sighing;
every night my tears wash over my bed,
soaking my couch with grief.

6.10:
All my enemies will crumble in shame;
shocked, they will retreat—
disgraced in a single moment.

19.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm of David.

The heavens pour forth declarations of God's glory;
the vault of the sky blazes with the story of his craft.

19.6:
It rises at one edge of the sky
and sweeps its great arc to the other side;
nothing in all creation is shielded from its heat.

20.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm of David.

May the LORD answer you when trouble closes in;
may the name of Jacob's God be your high tower.

20.5:
We will shout for joy when you are saved;
we will plant our banners in the name of our God.
May the LORD grant every request you have made.

20.6:
Now I know it for certain: the LORD delivers his anointed one.
He answers from his holy heaven;
from there his strong right arm brings deliverance.

21.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm of David.

The king exults in your power, LORD;
how greatly he rejoices in the victory you have given!

21.9:
You will make them like a furnace blazing before your face;
the LORD in his fury will consume them—
fire will swallow them whole.

22.15:
My strength crumbles like a broken shard;
my tongue sticks to the roof of my mouth.
You have brought me down to death's own dust.

22.16:
Dogs have surrounded me;
a pack of evildoers has closed in.
They have pierced my hands and my feet —

22.24:
For he has not despised the suffering of the one who suffers;
he has not turned his face away in disgust.
When that one cried out — he listened, he heard.

22.26:
The humble will eat their fill;
all who seek the LORD will praise him —
long life to your hearts!

22.29:
All the earth's well-fed will feast and bow before him;
all who descend to the dust will kneel —
even the one who could not keep himself alive.

23.3:
He brings my whole self back to life;
he guides me on the right paths
because that is who he is.

34.1:
A Psalm of David, when he feigned madness before Abimelech, who expelled him, and he went away.

I will bless the LORD at all times;
his praise will never leave my lips.

35.1:
A Psalm of David.

Take up my case, LORD, against those who take up arms against me;
fight those who fight me.

35.8:
Let devastation come on him out of nowhere;
let the very net he hid close around him;
let him plunge headlong into his own pit.

35.15:
But the moment I fell they celebrated and closed in;
strangers I had never known rallied against me
and tore at me without stopping.

35.17:
Lord — how long will you just look on?
Save my life from their rampage;
rescue my only life from the grip of these lions.

35.19:
Do not let my unjust enemies celebrate my fall;
do not let those who hate me for nothing
exchange triumphant glances.

36.3:
Everything he says breeds harm and lies;
he has abandoned wisdom
and cannot find his way to good.

36.4:
He lies on his bed planning trouble;
he puts himself on a road that leads nowhere good
and never turns away from evil.

36.6:
Your righteousness stands like the towering mountain ranges of God;
your justice runs as deep as the primordial ocean.
You preserve life, LORD — human life and animal life alike.

36.12:
There — look — the evildoers have fallen;
they were hurled down
and cannot rise again.

42.3:
I have eaten nothing but tears—day after day, night after night—
while all around me they keep asking:
'Where is this God of yours?'

43.1:
Judge my case, O God;
plead my cause against this godless nation —
deliver me from the man who is all lies and injustice.

44.8:
In God we have made our boast all day long;
your name we will praise to the ages.
Selah.

45.2:
You are the most beautiful of men;
what you say is filled with grace.
Therefore God has blessed you forever.

45.5:
Your arrows fly true;
nations collapse beneath you;
they pierce through the hearts of your enemies.

45.9:
Among your ladies of honor are daughters of kings;
and at your right hand stands the queen
dressed in the finest gold of Ophir.

45.14:
Robed in embroidered cloth she is led to the king;
her companions — the young women of her court —
follow behind her.

46.5:
God is within her — she will not be shaken;
God will come to her aid
when the morning comes.

46.7:
The LORD of hosts is with us;
the God of Jacob is our high fortress.
Selah.

46.10:
'Cease striving — and know that I am God.
I will be lifted high among the nations;
I will be lifted high over all the earth.'

46.11:
The LORD of hosts is with us;
the God of Jacob is our high fortress.
Selah.

47.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.

Clap your hands, all you peoples;
shout to God with a voice of triumph!

48.11:
Let Mount Zion shout with joy;
let every town of Judah be glad —
because of your righteous judgments.

50.3:
Our God comes—he does not come quietly.
Fire tears a path ahead of him;
a raging storm swirls all around him.

61.1:
To the worship leader, for stringed instruments. A Psalm of David.

Hear my cry, O God;
listen to my prayer.

61.5:
You have heard my vows, O God;
you have given me the inheritance
that belongs to all who revere your name.

61.7:
Let him dwell in God's presence forever;
appoint steadfast love and faithfulness
to be his constant guardians.

62.1:
To the worship leader, after the manner of Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.

In God alone my soul waits in silence;
from him comes all my salvation.

62.7:
My salvation and my honor rest in God;
he is the rock of my strength,
my refuge in every storm.

62.8:
Trust in him at every moment, all you people;
pour out your hearts before him —
God is our refuge. Selah.

63.11:
But the king will rejoice in God;
all who swear their loyalty to him will boast in him —
for every lying mouth will be shut.

64.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm of David.

Hear me, O God — my voice in distress;
guard my life from the terror the enemy brings.

64.3:
They grind their tongues sharp as swords;
they string the bow and take aim —
missiles of bitter, cutting words.

64.10:
The righteous will rejoice in the LORD
and find their shelter in him;
all the upright of heart will boast in God.

65.1:
To the worship leader. A Psalm. A Song of David.

To you, O God of Zion, praise gathers in silence;
to you every vow will be paid.

65.10:
You drench the furrows till they overflow;
you smooth the clods;
you soften the ground with gentle showers
and bless everything that springs up.

66.4:
All the earth bows before you;
they sing to you —
they sing praises to your name. Selah.

66.6:
He split the sea into dry ground;
they walked across the river on foot —
there we rejoiced in him.

66.7:
He governs by his power forever;
his eyes are fixed on every nation.
Let no rebel think they can rise above him. Selah.

66.12:
You let enemies ride roughshod over us;
we went through fire;
we went through flood —
but you brought us out
into an open and spacious place.

67.2:
Let it spread outward—
let the earth know what you are like,
let every nation see what it means to be rescued by you.

74.4:
Your enemies roared right inside your sacred courts;
they planted their own battle flags
where yours had stood.

74.16:
The day is yours;
the night belongs to you as well —
you set the sun and all its light in place.

76.1:
To the worship leader, with stringed instruments. A Psalm. A Song of Asaph.

God has made himself known in Judah;
his name is great across all Israel.

76.5:
The mighty warriors were plundered;
they have fallen into the sleep of death —
not one soldier could raise a hand.

76.10:
Even human rage ends up praising you;
whatever fury is left over,
you gird on like a weapon.

76.11:
Make your vows to the LORD your God and keep them;
let every nation around him bring tribute
to the one who inspires such dread.

79.1:
A Psalm of Asaph.

O God — the nations have stormed into your inheritance;
they have desecrated your holy temple;
they have left Jerusalem a heap of rubble.

79.8:
Do not hold our ancient sins against us;
let your compassion race ahead to meet us —
for we are sinking, brought as low as we can go.

79.11:
Let the groaning of the prisoner reach your ears;
by the might of your arm,
spare those who have been sentenced to death.

79.12:
Pay back our neighbors sevenfold —
let every insult they hurled at you, O Lord,
fall back into their own laps, multiplied.

80.3:
Restore us, O God —
let your face shine on us,
and we will be saved!

80.7:
Restore us, O God of hosts —
let your face shine on us,
and we will be saved!

80.9:
You prepared the soil before it;
it sank deep roots
and spread until it covered the land.

80.14:
Turn back to us, O God of hosts —
look down from heaven;
see it. Come and tend this vine.

80.15:
Look at what your right hand planted —
the vine you cultivated as your own;
look at the son you raised up in your strength.

80.19:
Restore us, O LORD God of hosts —
let your face shine on us,
and we will be saved!

81.7:
'You cried out in your trouble, and I came to rescue you;
I answered you from inside the thunder's hiding place.
I put you to the test at the waters of Meribah. Selah.'

81.16:
'I would have fed you the finest wheat;
with honey flowing from the rock
I would have satisfied you completely.'

82.1:
A Psalm of Asaph.

God has risen to stand in the divine assembly;
in the midst of the heavenly council he pronounces judgment:

82.7:
'And yet — you will die just like ordinary men;
you will fall like any other ruler
who failed those in his care.'

82.8:
Rise up, O God — judge the earth!
All the nations are your inheritance;
it is time to claim what is yours.

84.6:
As they pass through the valley of Baca — the valley of weeping —
they turn it into a place of springs;
the early rain clothes it with pools.

85.9:
Surely his rescue is near — close enough to touch —
for all who revere him,
so that his glory will take up residence in our land.

86.1:
A Prayer of David.

Bend your ear toward me, O LORD — answer me;
I have nothing, and I am desperate.

86.9:
Every nation you have made will come
and kneel before you, O Lord;
they will all bring glory to your name.

86.14:
O God — arrogant men have come after me;
a gang of violent people is hunting my life,
and they give no thought to you at all.

86.16:
Turn toward me — be gracious to me.
Give your servant your strength;
save the son of the woman who has devoted her life to you.

88.3:
My whole being is swamped with trouble;
I am being drawn toward Sheol —
the realm of the dead is pulling me in.

88.9:
My eyes have gone dull with weeping and grief.
Every day, O LORD, I call out to you;
I hold out my hands toward you.

88.15:
Since childhood I have lived in affliction, barely surviving —
your terrors have pressed down on me all my life;
I am overwhelmed and numb.

103.15:
As for mortal man—
his days are like grass.
He blooms like a wildflower of the field;

105.8:
He has remembered his covenant forever —
the word he proclaimed
for a thousand generations:

107.2:
Let the redeemed of the LORD say so—
those he has rescued
from the enemy's hand,

107.3:
gathered home from every land—
from east and west,
from north and south.

113.7:
He raises the poor from the dust —
he lifts the needy
from the ash heap,

120.2:
O LORD, deliver my soul
from lying lips,
from a tongue that deceives.

122.8:
For my brothers' sake,
for my companions' sake,
I say: 'Peace be within you!'

130.7:
O Israel — hope in the LORD!
With the LORD is steadfast love;
with him is plentiful redemption.

132.1:
A Song of Ascents.
O LORD, remember David —
remember all his hardships;

135.3:
Praise the LORD — for the LORD is good;
sing praises to his name,
for it is pleasant.

135.11:
Sihon, king of the Amorites;
Og, king of Bashan;
and all the kingdoms of Canaan —

135.17:
ears — but they cannot hear;
no breath at all
in their mouths.

138.1:
A Psalm of David.
With my whole heart I will praise you, O LORD;
before the heavenly council I will sing your praises.

139.20:
They speak against you with wicked purpose;
your enemies lift up your name
for nothing.

140.1:
For the choir director. A Psalm of David.
Deliver me, O LORD, from evil men;
preserve me from violent men.

141.3:
Set a guard over my mouth, O LORD;
keep watch
over the door of my lips.

142.1:
A Maskil. Of David. A prayer when he was in the cave.
With my full voice I cry to the LORD;
with my full voice I plead for his mercy.

142.2:
I pour out my complaint before him;
I lay my trouble
before him.

142.6:
Hear my cry — I am brought very low.
Deliver me from those who pursue me;
they are stronger than I am.

143.4:
My spirit grows faint within me;
my heart
is numb.

143.5:
I remember the days of old;
I meditate on all you have done —
I ponder the work of your hands.
